sentences: Kim Bo-mi (Korean: 김보미; born July 27, 1990), better known by her stage name, KittiB (Korean: 키디비), is a South Korean rapper and songwriter.
KittiB debuted in 2012 with the single, "I'm Her," which featured R&B singer Zion.
In 2015, she appeared on TV rap competition Unpretty Rapstar 2, where she ultimately placed second overall.
In April 2016, she appeared as a producer on JTBC's rap competition show, Tribe of Hip Hop, which pairs rappers with non-rapper celebrities to teach them hip-hop.
